Loading the dataset

Normalized, scaled dataset with information on the highest variable genes (HVGs).

seuset <- readRDS(paste0(dataset_location))
atlas_seuset <- readRDS(paste0(atlas_location))

Setting up results directory

dateoftoday <- gsub("-", "", as.character(Sys.Date()))
resultsdir <- paste(workdir, "/", dateoftoday, result_descript, "/", sep = "")
system(paste("mkdir -p ", resultsdir))
knitr::opts_knit$set(root.dir = normalizePath(resultsdir))

subsampled_data <- GetAssayData(subsampled, slot = "scale.data", assay = "RNA")
subsampled_coldata <- subsampled@meta.data[, c("seurat_clusters","Lineage"), drop = F]
subsampled_coldata <- subsampled_coldata[order(subsampled_coldata$seurat_clusters, decreasing = T),, drop = F]
subsampled_coldata <- subsampled_coldata[order(subsampled_coldata$Lineage, decreasing = T),, drop = F]
subsampled_data <- subsampled_data[,rownames(subsampled_coldata)]

atlas_data <- GetAssayData(sub_atlas, slot = "scale.data", assay = "sf")
atlas_coldata <- sub_atlas@meta.data[, c("seurat_clusters","Lineage"), drop = F]
atlas_coldata <- atlas_coldata[order(atlas_coldata$seurat_clusters, decreasing = T),, drop = F]
atlas_coldata <- atlas_coldata[order(atlas_coldata$Lineage, decreasing = T),, drop = F]

subsampled_data <- subsampled_data[rownames(subsampled_data) %in% rownames(seuset),]
atlas_data <- atlas_data[rownames(atlas_data) %in% rownames(subsampled_data),]

atlas_data <- atlas_data[rownames(subsampled_data),]

identical(rownames(atlas_data), rownames(subsampled_data))
## [1] TRUE
length(rownames(atlas_data))
## [1] 936
atlas_data <- as.matrix(atlas_data)
subsampled_data <- as.matrix(subsampled_data)
correlation_mat <- cor(atlas_data, subsampled_data, method = "pearson")
atlas_clust_col <- hue_pal()(length(unique(atlas_seuset@meta.data$seurat_clusters)))
names(atlas_clust_col) <- levels(atlas_seuset@meta.data$seurat_clusters)
colnames(atlas_coldata) <- c("atlas_clusters","Lineage")
subsampled_clust_col <- hue_pal()(length(levels(subsampled@meta.data$seurat_clusters)))
names(subsampled_clust_col) <- levels(subsampled@meta.data$seurat_clusters)
colnames(subsampled_coldata) <- c("multiome_clusters","Lineage")
lineage_col <- hue_pal()(2)
names(lineage_col) <- c("AM","VM")
rowAnn <- HeatmapAnnotation(df = atlas_coldata, name = "atlas cluster",
  which = 'row',col = list("Lineage" = lineage_col,"atlas_clusters" = atlas_clust_col),
  #col = colours,
  annotation_width = unit(c(1, 4), 'cm'),
  gap = unit(1, 'mm'))
colAnn <- HeatmapAnnotation(df = subsampled_coldata, name = "multiome cluster",
  which = 'col', col = list("Lineage" = lineage_col,"multiome_clusters" = subsampled_clust_col),
  #col = colours,
  annotation_width = unit(c(1, 4), 'cm'),
  gap = unit(1, 'mm'))

Heatmap(correlation_mat, cluster_columns = F, cluster_rows = F, show_column_names = F, show_row_names = F, left_annotation = rowAnn, top_annotation = colAnn)
pdf("CorrelationHeatmap_Multiome_d8EBAtlas_clusters.pdf", height = 15, width = 17)
Heatmap(correlation_mat, cluster_columns = F, cluster_rows = F, show_column_names = F, show_row_names = F, left_annotation = rowAnn, top_annotation = colAnn)
dev.off()

Plot markers of Atlas d8 clusters on Multiome data

seuset.markers <- read.csv(marker_genes_file, header = T, row.names = 1)
top_markers <- seuset.markers %>% group_by(cluster) %>% top_n(n = no_of_DEgenes, wt = avg_log2FC)
top_markers <- top_markers[top_markers$gene %in% rownames(seuset),]
pdf(paste0("Heatmap_top", no_of_DEgenes, "_markers_per_celltype.pdf"), height = 23, width = 13)
DoHeatmap(seuset, features = top_markers$gene, group.by = "seurat_clusters") + NoLegend()
